description: [8], 160, [12] p. : 25 cm. (fol.). First word of title transliterated from the Greek. Includes plants of American origin including adianthum from Brazil (the maidenhair fern), potatoes, here called solanum, and linaria americana, a flowering plant commonly called toadflax. Signatures: ):(⁴ ( ):(1 verso blank) A-X² Y². Errata: p. [12], 3rd count. Includes index. Text printed in two parallel columns. Engraved printer's ornament on title page; head and tail pieces; initials. "Nomina eorum, quorum opera in Prodromo adiuti fuimus": p. [8], 1st count. Purchase; 20-112
